an, and others and concludes that these writers still have much to teach us about changes in the nature of work and the emergence of a do-it-yourself ethos. DIY on the Lower East Side shows how place and politics shaped literature, and how New York City policies adopted at the time continue to shape our world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArtistsxHomes and hauntszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aArts, AmericanxEconomic aspectszNew York (State)zNew Yorky20th century. 0aGentrificationzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economic History. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Twentieth- and Twenty-First-Century Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847982840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479828423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479828/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles